---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Banner from '../components/Banner.astro';
import SectionHeader from '../components/SectionHeader.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Ayurveda"
  description="Learn what Ayurveda is, the three doshas, and how this ancient Indian science applies to modern life."
>
  <Banner
    title="About"
    titleEm="Ayurveda"
    subtitle="The ancient science of life"
  />

  <section class="bg-cream">
    <SectionHeader title="What is Ayurveda?" jp="アーユルヴェーダとは" />
    <div class="about-grid">
      <div class="about-text">
        <p>
          Ayurveda is one of the world's oldest and most complete systems of natural medicine,
          originating in ancient India over 5,000 years ago. The name itself unites two Sanskrit
          words: <em>Ayus</em> (life) and <em>Veda</em> (knowledge) — meaning "the science of life."
        </p>
        <p>
          Unlike modern medicine's focus on treating disease, Ayurveda sees health as a dynamic
          harmony between body, mind, and spirit. It teaches us how to understand our unique
          constitution — our <em>Prakriti</em> — and how to live in alignment with nature's rhythms
          through food, herbs, daily routine, and seasonal practice.
        </p>
        <p>
          At e-Ayurveda Osaka, we offer accessible, practical Ayurveda education grounded in
          authentic tradition, adapted thoughtfully for modern life in Japan and around the world.
        </p>
        <p style="margin-top:20px;">
          <a href="/courses" class="btn btn-primary">Explore Our Courses</a>
          &nbsp;&nbsp;
          <a href="/consultation" class="btn btn-outline">Book a Consultation</a>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="doshas-card">
        <h3>The Three Doshas</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Vata</strong> — Air &amp; Space. Governs movement, creativity, and the nervous
            system. When balanced: energetic and adaptable.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Pitta</strong> — Fire &amp; Water. Governs digestion, metabolism, and
            intelligence. When balanced: focused and purposeful.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Kapha</strong> — Earth &amp; Water. Governs structure, immunity, and stability.
            When balanced: calm and nurturing.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="doshas-note">
          Your unique combination of these three forces — your <em>Prakriti</em> — is determined
          at birth and guides every Ayurvedic recommendation.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 36px;
    align-items: start;
  }
  .about-text p { margin-bottom: 16px; font-size: 16.5px; color: var(--text); }
  .about-text p:first-child::first-letter {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 52px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--green-deep);
    float: left;
    line-height: 0.8;
    margin: 4px 8px 0 0;
  }
  .doshas-card {
    background: var(--green-deep);
    color: var(--white);
    padding: 28px 26px;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }
  .doshas-card h3 {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--gold-light);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    padding-bottom: 10px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(196,150,58,0.3);
    letter-spacing: 1px;
  }
  .doshas-card ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; }
  .doshas-card ul li {
    font-size: 14.5px;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.8);
    padding: 8px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
    display: flex;
    gap: 10px;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }
  .doshas-card ul li::before {
    content: '✦';
    color: var(--gold);
    font-size: 10px;
    margin-top: 4px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .doshas-note {
    margin-top: 18px;
    font-size: 13.5px;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  @media (max-width: 820px) {
    .about-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
